- **install git** - for the installation of git into the instance
- **git --v** - to check the version of git installed
- **apt install nodejs** - for the installation of nodejs into the instance
- **apt install npm** - for the installation of the packet manager
- **git clone** - for cloning the repository of the website to be hosted using the link of the repository from github
- **ls** - to check all the available files and folders
- **touch .env** - to make file using the .env extension for the environment set up
- **ls -a** - to check all the hidden files 
- **cat .env** - to check what is inside any file

